    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-06-01T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-06-01T10:00:00-05:00" n="212"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d212">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24 Raw Materials/156a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-06-01T11:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 1, 1939—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>400. Department would appreciate report on status discussions with the British
                    Government regarding cotton–tin–rubber deal.</p>
                <p>We had hoped the matter might be concluded in time to submit agreement and
                    necessary legislation to this session of Congress. Present circumstances seem
                    more propitious for concluding deal than future circumstances may be. Further
                    delay would probably mean change in relative market situations of the
                    commodities compelling modifications in the terms of the agreement.</p>
                <p>Conclusion of this deal would I think have good general effect on American
                    opinion in regard to various other matters likely to come before Congress in the
                    near future.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
